cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of a cooperative cognitive radio network, which involves communication between multiple nodes. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the analysis of the probability of successful symbol transmission, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the interference from primary transmitters, which can be seen as a security threat to the secondary transmitter. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the analysis of the performance of a system (the cooperative cognitive radio network) and the trade-off between energy harvesting and interference. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper involves the cooperation between multiple nodes in the network, which can be seen as a multiagent system.
